<title type="html"><![CDATA[Microphone Schematics for NES, NES2 and New FC]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7094&amp;p=69080#p69080"><![CDATA[
I was asked to do a little research into the FC microphone, and how to make it functional on the New Famicom (A/V). In the process, so far, I have <a href="http://www.atariusa.com/Famicom_Schematics/Microphone" class="postlink">whipped up a schematic for the microphone circuitry</a>... <br /><br />The New FC and NES2 use a unified custom IC in place of the 40H368. so for those who want to make the mic work on your system, you'll essentially need to build this using a 40H368, or compatible part. The NES still uses the 40H368, so all I presume that you'd need to do is add the additional circuitry, however, this is (at present) untested and unverified.<br /><br />If you find any error in the design, please point it out and feel free to make corrections, suggestions or the usual ridicule as necessary.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4070">Xious</a> â€” Mon Oct 25, 2010 9:00 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
